observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
Strictly observe the pertinent provisions of RA No. 9184 and its applicable IRR, such that all procurements must be conducted through public bidding. Alternative methods of procurement must be resorted to only in highly exceptional cases provided for in RA No. 9184;
Require the BAC to supervise all types of procurement, not just infrastructure projects but also goods, pursuant to Section 11.1 of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A No. 9184;
Discontinue procurement through reimbursement basis unless extremely urgent, necessary and in small amount; and
Ensure that an APP is prepared to support the Annual Budget of the LGU which must incorporate all its procurement requirements for each calendar year, to avoid audit disallowance thereof.

Immediately formulate a 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan (SWMP). This must be reviewed and approved by the National Solid Waste Management Commission (NSWMC). Review by the NSWMC of the said plan will assess if it addresses the necessary issues concerning Solid Waste Management in the Municipality. Moreover, necessary requirements are needed for the approval of the SWMP;

Strictly comply with RA No. 9003 on the establishment of Solid Waste and Material Recovery Facility (MRF); and

Exert continuous effort in educating the people of Monreal on the importance of Solid Waste Management.

a. Require the Inventory Committee and the General Services Officer to conduct physical count of the Municipality’s PPE and prepare the Report as prescribed under Section 57, Volume II of NGAS Manual and submit the same to the Local Chief Executive and Auditor;

b. Require the General Services Officer/Municipal Treasurer to maintain stock cards/records on all properties of the agency; and

c. Require the Municipal Accountant to properly maintain ledger cards of all properties. This must be reconciled with stock/property cards maintained by the GSO or Municipal Treasurer
